{"model": "Qwen 3.5 122B-A10B (MoE)", "runtime": "llamacpp", "prompt_name": "math_multiply__t2_cot", "prompt_tokens": 0, "generation_tokens": 0, "prompt_tps": 136.4, "generation_tps": 41.0, "peak_memory_gb": 0.0, "wall_time_sec": 30.1, "output": "To calculate $47 \\times 89$, we can use the standard multiplication algorithm or break the numbers down using the distributive property.\n\n**Method 1: Long Multiplication**\n\n1.  Multiply 47 by the ones digit of 89 (which is 9):\n    *   $7 \\times 9 = 63$ (write 3, carry 6)\n    *   $4 \\times 9 = 36$\n    *   $36 + 6 = 42$\n    *   Result: **423**\n\n2.  Multiply 47 by the tens digit of 89 (which is 8), remembering this represents 80:\n    *   $7 \\times 8 = 56$ (write 6, carry 5)\n    *   $4 \\times 8 = 32$\n    *   $32 + 5 = 37$\n    *   Result: **376** (which is 3760)\n\n3.  Add the two partial results together:\n    ```\n      423\n    +3760\n    -----\n     4183\n    ```\n\n**Method 2: Distributive Property**\n\nRewrite 89 as $(90 - 1)$:\n$$47 \\times 89 = 47 \\times (90 - 1)$$\n$$= (47 \\times 90) - (47 \\times 1)$$\n\nCalculate $47 \\times 90$:\n$$47 \\times 9 = 423$$\n$$423 \\times 10 = 4230$$\n\nSubtract 47:\n$$4230 - 47 = 4183$$\n\nBoth methods give the same result.\n\nANSWER: 4183", "error": null, "prompt_hash": "f2fc3608f651", "quant": "Q4_K_M"}
